Technorati-Ruby 0.1.0 README
============================

This document was last updated on Wed Sep 29 09:29:19 2004.  Please see
the file COPYING for licensing and warranty information.  Visit
http://pablotron.org/software/technorati-ruby/ for the latest version of
this software.

Overview
========
Technorati (http://technorati.com/) bindings for Ruby.  You'll need to
create an account at Technorati and obtain an API key in order to use
Technorati-Ruby.  An RDoc-generated API reference is in doc/, and some
simple examples are in examples/.

Requirements
============
* Ruby (http://www.ruby-lang.org/), version 1.8.0 (or newer).
* ParseDate (included with Ruby 1.8.x).
* REXML (included with Ruby 1.8.x).

Installation
============
# copy technorati lib to site_ruby dir
cp technorati.rb /usr/local/lib/site_ruby/1.8/

  or (if you have RubyGems installed)

# build and install RubyGem
gem build technorati.gemspec && gem install *.gem

